image.altText: A picture of two men is cropped into a bigger image of the front of a home with dozens of flowers laid out the front.

props.synopsis: NSW Police will continue investigating a property in Bungonia overnight where two bodies were found as a vigil is held for Sydney couple Jesse Baird and Luke Davies.

title.children: Tributes shared for Sydney couple as police remain at crime scene where two bodies were found

image.altText: An army tank

props.synopsis: An Israeli company whose technology was stripped from Australian Army equipment over possible data security concerns three years ago has been awarded a fresh defence contract worth $600 million.

title.children: Controversial Israeli weapons company awarded $600 million Australian army contract

image.altText: A young woman with blonde hair sits at a computer desk, it is covered with stationary.

props.synopsis: It's official, men are paid more than women at many of the country's major companies, including banks, retailers, legal firms and mines, but what is being done to address it?

title.children: Workplace lawyers say it's time to ask questions about why men are paid more

image.altText: Charred bushland following a fire

props.synopsis: Hot temperatures and strong winds are expected in Victoria and South Australia, with hundreds of firefighters deployed to contain potential outbreaks.

title.children: Victoria braces for another day of 'catastrophic' fire danger, a week on from bushfires that destroyed six homes

image.altText: Coles and Woolworths branding outside neighbouring supermarkets

props.synopsis: Accusations of price gouging have again been levelled at Coles after the supermarket giant revealed another bumper profit.

title.children: 'No-one has to earn a 30pc profit rate': Coles accused of gouging shoppers as they struggle to put food on table

image.altText: A text message reading: 'Medicare: Due to the recent abnormal operation of your Medicare, we have to suspend your service.'

props.synopsis: Australian authorities say the newest scam threatens to suspend or freeze Medicare accounts.

title.children: Authorities say 'spike' in Medicare scam text messages

image.altText: A woman using a smartphone surrounded by beams of light

props.synopsis: The internet is filling up with machine-generated "zombie content" designed to game algorithms and scam humans. Experts call it the "great AI flood".

title.children: Twitter is becoming a 'ghost town' of bots as AI content floods the internet

image.altText: Metal band Scaphis standing outside and smiling

props.synopsis: Hitler salutes, white supremacy slogans and symbols of hate … insiders say Nazi bands have become an open secret within Australia's metal scene, as fans prepare for the return of major international event Knotfest next month.

title.children: The dark side of metal music

image.altText: A woman with blonde hair looks to the side, as a man in a suit stares ahead.

props.synopsis: WA Liberal Leader Libby Mettam dismisses her deputy leader Steve Thomas after it emerges he used disgraced former premier Brian Burke as a middleman to secure a meeting.

title.children: WA Liberal leader sacks her deputy for enlisting help of disgraced former premier and denying it

image.altText: A mug shot of a bald man in his twenties

props.synopsis: Joshua Duperouzel is sentenced to life in prison after he shot dead a man at a semi-rural property in Perth because believed he owed a $3,000 debt.

title.children: Man given life sentence after shooting dead another man over alleged $3,000 drug debt

image.altText: Prince William looking concerned

props.synopsis: Prince William has pulled out of attending a memorial service at Windsor Castle for his godfather, the late King Constantine of Greece, because of an unspecified personal matter, his office said.

title.children: Prince William pulls out of memorial service for late godfather, citing 'personal matter'

image.altText: A close portrait of a woman in business attire, who is looking at the camera with a neutral expression.

props.synopsis: NDIS Quality and Safeguards Commissioner Tracey Mackey announces she will "embark on new career opportunities" just two days before an independent report investigating a scandal exposed by Four Corners is due.

title.children: NDIS commissioner resigns days before report due into scandal exposed by Four Corners

image.altText: Scott Morrison gestures while standing in the House of Representatives

props.synopsis: Australia's 30th Prime Minister is finally about to leave the building, almost two years after losing the federal election. Defeated PMs tend not to hang around for this long, but as a wise man once said, "It's not a race", writes Annabel Crabb.

title.children: Known for walking on both sides of the street, Morrison kept it up until the very end

image.altText: Albanese looks up while standing at a lectern, an Australian flag behind him.

props.synopsis: The government's overhaul of the stage 3 tax cuts passed the Senate unamended on Tuesday evening, having previously passed in the House of Representatives. The tax cuts will now become law.

title.children: Government's overhaul of stage 3 tax cuts pass Senate

image.altText: Former rugby league great Wally Lewis smiles for the cameras as he holds an orange t-shirt tagged "you only get one brain".

props.synopsis: Rugby league great Wally Lewis goes to Canberra to meet politicians, share his experiences of short-term memory loss and call for federal money to be put towards education and support for the fight against chronic traumatic encephalopathy (CTE).

title.children: 'My diary ... is my best friend': League great Wally Lewis urges politicians to put CTE funding in budget

image.altText: The rear of a plane with wheels down about to land on a runway

props.synopsis: As Tasmanians get ready to vote in a state election, experts are predicting a gloomy time ahead for the state, with a shrinking population and economic downturn expected.

title.children: People aren't moving to Tasmania any more, making for 'a very volatile situation'

image.altText: Two officers hold a banner saying Australian Federal Police in the Mardi Gras parade

props.synopsis: An AFP spokesperson says they will not march in the Sydney Gay and Lesbian Mardi Gras this year, following the alleged murders of Jesse Baird and Luke Davies.

title.children: 'We understand their hurt': Australian Federal Police decide not to march at Mardi Gras

image.altText: Nurse standing outside.

props.synopsis: Rural hospitals across Australia are struggling to attract and retain nursing staff. An outback campus in Queensland is addressing the issue by training staff locally, but the union says more opportunities are needed.

title.children: Number of student nurses in outback region triples in three years as education shifts from bigger towns

image.altText: Red dirt and blue sky at a cobalt mine in Broken Hill.

props.synopsis: Cobalt Blue will undertake a strategic review of its Broken Hill Cobalt Project after the price of cobalt dropped. Originally set to create 400 jobs, that number will now fall.

title.children: Australian-first 'ethically sourced' cobalt project hits major speedbump due to global oversupply

image.altText: close up of a barista's hands making coffee into an aqua coloured mug

props.synopsis: Last year Labor passed legislation to criminalise wage theft, but its legislation did not fulfil part of its promise, according to experts.

title.children: Labor's promise to criminalise wage theft without overriding state laws is stalled. Here's why

image.altText: A white man in a blue collared shirt, surrounded by reporters and cameras. A sign behind him says 'Local Court'.

props.synopsis: Outback Wrangler star Matt Wright has indicated he will fight charges laid by the Northern Territory's work safety watchdog over a fatal helicopter crash that killed his co-star Chris "Willow" Wilson.

title.children: Matt Wright and company Helibrook to contest WorkSafe NT charges over chopper crash

image.altText: A coach wearing a NSW women's State of Origin jacket looks across at a questioner during a press conference.

props.synopsis: NSW State of Origin coach Kylie Hilder calls for the NRL to wait until 2026 to expand the women's competition to 12 teams, one year later than expected.

title.children: Hold off NRLW expansion until 2026, says NSW Origin coach

image.altText: An explosion on a beach.

props.synopsis: The girl and her stepdad got quite a fright when they chanced across the explosive device, which was destroyed on the beach at Ulladulla.

title.children: Footage shows detonation of explosive device picked up by girl collecting shells before school

image.altText: An illustration of a person looking sad in a group in front of a rainbow background

props.synopsis: LGBTQ+ Australians are experiencing mental illness and self harm at rates sometimes "more than double" their heterosexual counterparts, new data released by the Australian Bureau of Statistics reveals.

title.children: 'Discrimination, assault and harassment': New data paints a 'sobering' picture of mental health for LGBTQ+ Australians

image.altText: Image of Joe Biden talking, he is wearing a blue suit with a tie with tiny donkeys on it. Behind him are green leaves .

props.synopsis: US President Joe Biden says Israel has agreed to halt military activities in Gaza for the Muslim holy month of Ramadan if Hamas accepts its prisoner-hostage deal.

title.children: Biden says Israel agrees to stop Gaza attacks during Ramadan if hostage deal is reached

props.synopsis: A Gold Coast magistrate has ordered Eddie Hayson's extradition to Sydney, where he will face court later this week.

title.children: Punter and former brothel owner Eddie Hayson arrested after drug syndicate probe

image.altText: A close up photo taken by a lunar lander near the surface of the Moon

props.synopsis: A private US Moon lander is expected to stop working days before originally planned, while a Japanese one is again showing signs of life.

title.children: US Moon lander mission cut short after landing sideways as Japan's lander survives another lunar night

image.altText: Taylor Swift, and Scott Swift cheer while watching the game at Gillette Stadium on December 17, 2023

props.synopsis: Sydney paparazzo photographer Ben McDonald says Scott Swift assaulted him after his daughter had disembarked a cruise on Sydney Harbour.

title.children: 'He's punched me in the face': Sydney photographer accuses Taylor Swift's father of assault

image.altText: A composite image of two people lying in hospital beds.

props.synopsis: The number of Australians who received a kidney from a living donor was back to pre-COVID levels last year, helped along by a record year for a program that allows people to donate to strangers.

title.children: Nico gave his kidney to a stranger to save his wife Belinda — and other anonymous donors are doing the same
